          <PdfSlideCarousel
            client:visible
            src="/pitch-deck.pdf"
            aspectRatio={16 / 9}
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>
            This project was initially pitched to act as a springboard for
            non-designers to get a better glimpse into the world of design. I
            believe that most people care about the way their apps are designed,
            because the majority of people I know complain about issues they see
            in the apps they interact with every day.
          </p>
          <br />
          <p>
            As such, the plan was to go term-by-term through each UX principle
            and provide an explanation in detail of what it is, where you'll
            find it, and why it's effective. But, seeing that we are living in
            an <a href="https://claude.ai/chat" target="_blank">age of AI</a>, I
            concluded that would be more effective to teach by <i>example</i>,
            using interactive demos as a springboard to teach these principles.
          </p>
          <br />
          <p>
            Using demos to teach content is a great tool to package information
            in a way that shows, rather than tells. Not only does it make the
            glossary more engaging, but it differentiates this resource from
            others on the market, such as <a
              href="https://coglode.com/"
              target="_blank">Coglode</a
            >. The iteration speed AI affords is the only way I was able to
            build in as much interactivity as I ended up with.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

